Daily totals (by trip date)
DEFINE
    MEASURE 'Actual Trips'[Total Passenger] = SUM('Actual Trips'[Passengers On])
EVALUATE
SUMMARIZECOLUMNS(
    'Actual Trips'[Trip Date],
    "Total Passenger", [Total Passenger],
    "Trips", COUNTROWS('Actual Trips')
)

Output: one row per Trip Date with total passengers + trip count.
Monthly totals (using a calendar/date dimension
DEFINE
    MEASURE 'Actual Trips'[Total Passenger] = SUM('Actual Trips'[Passengers On])
EVALUATE
SUMMARIZECOLUMNS(
    'Date'[Year],
    'Date'[MonthNumber],          -- use MonthNumber to order properly
    'Date'[MonthName],
    "Total Passenger", [Total Passenger],
    "Trips", COUNTROWS('Actual Trips')
)
ORDER BY 'Date'[Year], 'Date'[MonthNumber]

DEFINE
    MEASURE 'Actual Trips'[Total Passenger] = SUM('Actual Trips'[Passengers On])
EVALUATE
SUMMARIZECOLUMNS(
    'Date'[Year],
    'Date'[MonthNumber],          -- use MonthNumber to order properly
    'Date'[MonthName],
    "Total Passenger", [Total Passenger],
    "Trips", COUNTROWS('Actual Trips')
)
ORDER BY 'Date'[Year], 'Date'[MonthNumber]

Use a proper date dimension (recommended) for correct time intelligence and ordering.
Totals by route

DEFINE
    MEASURE 'Actual Trips'[Total Passenger] = SUM('Actual Trips'[Passengers On])
EVALUATE
SUMMARIZECOLUMNS(
    'Actual Trips'[Route],
    "Total Passenger", [Total Passenger],
    "Trips", COUNTROWS('Actual Trips')
)
ORDER BY [Total Passenger] DESC

Totals by driver (driver in same table)

DEFINE
    MEASURE 'Actual Trips'[Total Passenger] = SUM('Actual Trips'[Passengers On])
EVALUATE
SUMMARIZECOLUMNS(
    'Actual Trips'[Driver],
    "Total Passenger", [Total Passenger],
    "Trips", COUNTROWS('Actual Trips')
)
ORDER BY [Total Passenger] DESC

If drivers are in a separate dimension table (Drivers[Name]), use that column instead:

Combined breakdown: date × route × driver

DEFINE
    MEASURE 'Actual Trips'[Total Passenger] = SUM('Actual Trips'[Passengers On])
EVALUATE
SUMMARIZECOLUMNS(
    'Actual Trips'[Trip Date],
    'Actual Trips'[Route],
    'Actual Trips'[Driver],
    "Total Passenger", [Total Passenger],
    "Trips", COUNTROWS('Actual Trips')
)
ORDER BY 'Actual Trips'[Trip Date], [Total Passenger] DESC

Use paging/filters if the result set is large.
Top N drivers by total passengers (overall) Option A — using SUMMARIZE + TOPN:

EVALUATE
TOPN(
  10,
  SUMMARIZE(
    'Actual Trips',
    'Actual Trips'[Driver],
    "TotalPassenger", SUM('Actual Trips'[Passengers On])
  ),
  [TotalPassenger],
  DESC
)

Option B — using ADDCOLUMNS + VALUES

EVALUATE
TOPN(
  10,
  ADDCOLUMNS(
    VALUES('Actual Trips'[Driver]),
    "TotalPassenger", CALCULATE(SUM('Actual Trips'[Passengers On]))
  ),
  [TotalPassenger],
  DESC
)

EVALUATE
TOPN(
  10,
  ADDCOLUMNS(
    VALUES('Actual Trips'[Driver]),
    "TotalPassenger", CALCULATE(SUM('Actual Trips'[Passengers On]))
  ),
  [TotalPassenger],
  DESC
)
Filtering by date range, specific route, or driver (like WHERE) Example — last 30 days and only Route 'A':
SQL
DEFINE
    MEASURE 'Actual Trips'[Total Passenger] = SUM('Actual Trips'[Passengers On])
EVALUATE
SUMMARIZECOLUMNS(
    'Actual Trips'[Trip Date],
    'Actual Trips'[Route],
    "Total Passenger", [Total Passenger],
    FILTER(
      'Actual Trips',
      'Actual Trips'[Trip Date] >= TODAY() - 30
      && 'Actual Trips'[Route] = "A"
    )
)
Or use KEEPFILTERS inside CALCULATE for more complex logic.

Get totals ignoring report/page filters (absolute totals)
SQL
DEFINE
    MEASURE 'Actual Trips'[Total Passenger All] =
        CALCULATE( SUM('Actual Trips'[Passengers On]), ALL('Actual Trips') )
EVALUATE
SUMMARIZECOLUMNS(
    'Actual Trips'[Route],
    "Total Passenger (All Filters Ignored)", [Total Passenger All]
)
Additional useful columns
Average passengers per trip: ADDCOLUMNS or create a measure: AveragePassengers = DIVIDE([Total Passenger], COUNTROWS('Actual Trips'))
Percent of total (by route/driver): % of Total = DIVIDE([Total Passenger], CALCULATE([Total Passenger], ALL('Actual Trips')))
Performance & practical tips
Prefer SUMMARIZECOLUMNS for performance and to respect filter context; use VALUES/ADDCOLUMNS when you need calculated columns per group.
For large datasets limit rows (filters, TOPN) or aggregate at higher granularity (month instead of day).
Keep numeric columns typed correctly (Passengers On must be numeric).
Use a proper date dimension for consistent time-based groupings and to leverage time-intelligence functions.
If you need subtotals/rollups, consider building separate queries for each level (or use DAX functions for subtotals — SUMMARIZECOLUMNS doesn’t auto-insert hierarchical subtotals).
Example expected output (conceptual)

By Route: Route | Total Passenger | Trips | Avg Per Trip R1 | 12,340 | 1,234 | 10.0 R2 | 8,900 | 890 | 10.0
